{
  "stem": "23428.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That means my grandfather came to Breslau as a very young man, as a boy, I understand 14 or 15 years old, from a little place close to Posen-- it's now Poznan, called Wisla, and-- and started working in a bank at age 15, I think, in Breslau, then stayed there over-- over his whole entire life, became a very wealthy banker and industrialist.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's my paternal grandfather.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Carl Chrambach.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He always had jobs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, his first job starting [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] maybe two or three years prior to World War I was to become a professional German soldier.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at the end of World War I, he emerged from this as-- with a rank above lieutenant and below captain.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know the English expression for it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he quit the army with-- when the Republic was created in Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then after spent I think a couple of years in what is called in German the Freikorps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Freikorps were right-wing groups, mostly made up of old army soldiers who were fighting Communists in the streets of Germany for control of the country.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when he-- when that came to an end with the firm establishment of the Social Democratic government and liberal Weimar Republic, he became a banker.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In fact, he with a colleague, I think, were acquired a bank, a private bank, I suspect with the good offices of my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he was a banker until the world bank crash in 1929 or possibly '31.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm not sure about that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think it's 29.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then he-- he became the chief administrator in a compound of industrial and agricultural estates that belonged to a Prince Hohenlohe, Hohenlohe [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
